# Cloudflare Workers MCP patterns

## Exports

- The McpAgent subclass must be a **named export** (Wrangler requires it for DO bindings).
- The fetch handler must be the **default export**.
- Both live in `src/index.ts`.

## Wrangler

- `compatibility_flags: ["nodejs_compat"]` is required — without it the `agents` package fails at runtime.
- Each DO migration needs a unique `tag`. Add a new migration object when changing DO state schema.

## McpAgent

- `this.env` provides all Cloudflare bindings and secrets.
- `this.ctx.storage` provides persistent state that survives DO eviction.
- Instance variables survive between tool calls within the same session but are lost on eviction.
- `McpAgent.serve("/mcp")` in the fetch handler routes to the DO.
- For EU jurisdiction: `McpAgent.serve("/mcp", { jurisdiction: "eu" })`.

## Secrets

- Local dev: `.dev.vars` (auto-read by `wrangler dev`).
- Production: `echo "value" | npx wrangler secret put SECRET_NAME`.
- Keep both in sync — this is the most common error source.

## Tool registration

- Use `registerXxxTools(server, ...deps)` functions — one per tool group.
- Every Zod parameter needs `.describe()` — the LLM uses descriptions to fill arguments.
- Return meaningful error messages as `content: [{ type: "text", text: "..." }]` — the LLM can retry based on them.

## Stateful vs stateless

| Approach | Stateful? | Requires DO? | Best for |
|---|---|---|---|
| `createMcpHandler()` | No | No | Stateless tools, simple setup |
| `McpAgent` | Yes | Yes | Session state, elicitation |

## OAuth with upstream provider

- Default export changes from `{ fetch() }` to `new OAuthProvider({...})`.
- McpAgent gets a generic type parameter: `McpAgent<Env, unknown, UpstreamOAuthProps>`.
- OAuth tokens arrive via `this.props.accessToken` in `init()`.
- Store refreshed tokens in `this.ctx.storage` — they survive DO eviction.
- KV namespace (`OAUTH_KV`) required for OAuth state management.
- Hono app handles `/authorize` and `/callback` flow.
- `workers-oauth-utils.ts` provides CSRF, state management, approval dialog — this file is generic and can be copied between projects.
- Email restrictions via `ALLOWED_EMAIL_DOMAIN` (comma-separated domains) and `ALLOWED_EMAILS` (comma-separated specific addresses).
- Required packages: `@cloudflare/workers-oauth-provider`, `hono`.

## Testing

- MCP Inspector: `npx @modelcontextprotocol/inspector@latest`
- Connect to local: `http://localhost:8788/mcp`
- Connect to deployed: `https://<worker>.workers.dev/mcp`
